  "text": "## Envoy Extension Registry Pattern Implementation\n\nThe Envoy proxy implements an extension registry pattern that enables dynamic, compile-time discovery and registration of extension factories. The architecture consists of several key components:\n\n### Core Components\n\n**1. Registry Template Class (envoy/registry/registry.h:166)**\nThe `FactoryRegistry<Base>` template class is the central registry that manages all factory instances for a given base class. It maintains:\n- A static factory map (hash map from name to factory pointer)\n- Factories indexed by configuration type\n- Versioning information for vendor-specific factories\n- Deprecated factory name mappings\n\nKey methods:\n- `getFactory(name)` - Lookup factory by string name\n- `getFactoryByType(type_url)` - Lookup by protobuf type\n- `registerFactory(Base& factory, absl::string_view name)` - Runtime registration\n- `registeredNames()` - List all registered factories\n\n**2. RegisterFactory Template Class (envoy/registry/registry.h:507)**\nThe `RegisterFactory<T, Base>` template enables static registration of factory instances. When instantiated (typically at module load time), the constructor:\n1. Creates a static instance of the concrete factory (T)\n2. Registers it with `FactoryRegistry<Base>::registerFactory()`\n3. Registers the factory's category with `FactoryCategoryRegistry`\n\nThe RegisterFactory constructor supports multiple overloads for:\n- Basic registration\n- Registration with deprecated names\n- Registration with vendor-specific versions (major, minor, patch)\n\n**3. Macros (envoy/registry/registry.h:618-654)**\nTwo macro variants handle static registration:\n\n`REGISTER_FACTORY(FACTORY, BASE)` - When `ENVOY_STATIC_EXTENSION_REGISTRATION` is defined:\n```cpp\nstatic Envoy::Registry::RegisterFactory<FACTORY, BASE> FACTORY##_registered;\n```\n\nWhen not defined, it generates a function that dynamically creates the RegisterFactory:\n```cpp\nvoid forceRegister##FACTORY() {\n  static auto registered = new Envoy::Registry::RegisterFactory<FACTORY, BASE>();\n}\n```\n\n**4. Factory Base Classes (envoy/config/typed_config.h)**\n- `UntypedFactory` - Base with `name()` and `category()` methods\n- `TypedFactory` - Extends UntypedFactory with `createEmptyConfigProto()` for protobuf configuration\n\n### Self-Registration at Static Initialization\n\nThe pattern leverages C++ static initialization to register factories:\n\n1. **Compile-time registration** (typical): Extensions define a static instance of `RegisterFactory<ConcreteFactory, BaseFactory>` at file scope, which runs during program initialization.\n\n2. **Example from source/extensions/filters/http/geoip/config.cc:35-36**:\n```cpp\nREGISTER_FACTORY(GeoipFilterFactory,\n                 Server::Configuration::NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory){\"envoy.geoip\"};\n```\nThis expands to a static `RegisterFactory` instance that registers `GeoipFilterFactory` under the name \"envoy.geoip\".\n\n3. **Factory Category Registry**: Each factory also registers its category string (`UntypedFactory::category()` method) with `FactoryCategoryRegistry`, enabling discovery by category.\n\n### Factory Lookup Pattern\n\nAt runtime, extensions are discovered via two mechanisms:\n\n1. **By name lookup** (envoy/registry/registry.h:293):\n```cpp\nBase* getFactory(absl::string_view name) {\n  auto it = factories().find(name);\n  return (it == factories().end()) ? nullptr : it->second;\n}\n```\n\n2. **By protobuf type** (envoy/registry/registry.h:302):\nThe `factoriesByType()` map is lazily built from all registered factories' `configTypes()`, enabling type-based lookup.\n\n### Configuration Implementation Files\n\n**Context and Utility Files:**\n- `source/server/factory_context_impl.h` - FactoryContextImplBase for factory creation contexts\n- `source/server/configuration_impl.h` - StatsSinkFactory and configuration management\n- `source/common/config/utility.h` - Utility functions like `getAndCheckFactoryByName()` and `translateToFactoryConfig()`\n\n**Test Utilities (test/test_common/registry.h):**\n- `InjectFactory<Base>` - Temporarily replaces a factory for testing\n- `InjectFactoryCategory<Base>` - Registers a test category\n\n### Extension Implementation Pattern\n\nEach extension (found throughout source/extensions/) implements this pattern:\n\n1. **Header file** (e.g., config.h): Defines a factory class inheriting from `Config::TypedFactory` or base class specific to that extension type\n2. **Implementation file** (e.g., config.cc): \n   - Implements `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` or equivalent\n   - Uses `REGISTER_FACTORY` macro at file scope for static registration\n   - Looks up other factories via `Registry::FactoryRegistry<T>::getFactory()`\n\nExamples of this pattern appear in:\n- HTTP filters (geoip, grpc_web, wasm, connect_grpc_bridge)\n- Listener filters (tls_inspector, http_inspector, original_dst, proxy_protocol)\n- Access loggers (fluentd, open_telemetry, stream)\n- Tracers (opentelemetry, skywalking)\n- Load balancing policies (maglev, cluster_provided)\n- Stat sinks (dog_statsd, hystrix)\n- And many more (48+ files in source/extensions/)\n\n### Thread Safety\n\nThe registry is **not thread-safe** during registration. Registration must occur in a single-threaded environment, guaranteed by static initialization happening before main() executes. All factory lookups after initialization are safe for concurrent access since the maps are only read, not modified.\n"
